The paired fibrous structures arising from the cervix and attaching to the lateral pelvic walls at the level of the ischial spines are the cardinal ligaments. Each cardinal ligament contains the uterine artery, which supplies blood to the uterus. Superior vesical artery supplies blood to the bladder, artery of Sampson is not a recognized vessel in medicine, and ovarian artery supplies blood to the ovaries.
